{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"550f76cf-87f0-4537-be08-4e4ceb101155","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four surface the reason string in test results so you can track why each test was skipped.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f242bcbc-74ae-4462-a2ed-3d67df577f1e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question about test framework APIs. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":206,"requestId":"0847:44A9F:7F085FA:8D636BE:69EAC2A2"},"id":"b1c38c1d-700a-4e7e-bfaf-ca3e57b90278","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:08:55.806Z","parentId":"45eb82cd-1db4-41e7-a3dd-afe6fee786ec"}
